{"type": "article", "id": 443, "title": "Autodesk 进军硬件，要做 3D 打印机的 Android", "description": "计算机辅助设计软件巨头 Autodesk 也开始做硬件了，它要在 3D 打印机的世界里构筑一个类似 Android 的开放平台。", "date": "2014-05-15T11:26:52Z", "super_tag": null, "tags": [{"id": 571, "name": "Autodesk"}, {"id": 572, "name": "3D 打印"}, {"id": 216, "name": "创客"}, {"id": 143, "name": "设计"}, {"id": 511, "name": "硬件"}], "category": 4, "author": 3, "comment_count": 0, "praise_count": 6, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160605203720W7zFfD3CZ260oxYO.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p class=\"p1\">\r\n\t<span class=\"s2\" style=\"line-height:1.5;\">Autodesk </span><span style=\"line-height:1.5;\">是一家以设计软件著称的公司，产品覆盖建筑、工业生产乃至电影动画等不同领域的设计。从特斯拉的办公室到中国二线城市街边的小作坊，都少不了</span><span class=\"s2\" style=\"line-height:1.5;\"> AutoCAD</span><span style=\"line-height:1.5;\">。</span> \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">\r\n\t现在这家总部位于旧金山的公司不满足于计算机辅助设计，开始自己做硬件。<span class=\"s2\">Autodesk </span>的首款硬件产品将是一台桌面<span class=\"s2\"> 3D </span>打印机，远观酷似自动浓缩咖啡机。这台<span class=\"s2\"> 3D </span>打印机将采用<span class=\"s2\"> SLA </span>技术，通过紫外光将树脂凝固起来，构成设计师想要的样子。该技术精度较高，以往多被用于工业级产品，<span class=\"s2\">Autodesk </span>的打印机将成为少数几款采用<span class=\"s2\"> SLA </span>的桌面级<span class=\"s2\"> 3D </span>打印机。\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">\r\n\t<span class=\"s2\">Autodesk </span>表示自己推出<span class=\"s2\"> 3D </span>打印机并不想直接和<span class=\"s2\"> MakerBot </span>等产品竞争，而是作为参考设计，展示自己的<span class=\"s2\"> <a href=\"http://www.autodesk.com/spark#sthash.kxgnUPv2.dpuf\">3D <span class=\"s1\">打印软件平台</span> Spark</a></span>。\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">\r\n\t<span class=\"s2\">“</span>这款<span class=\"s2\"> 3D </span>打印机将展示<span class=\"s2\"> Spark </span>平台的实力，为<span class=\"s2\"> 3D </span>打印体验设立标杆。<span class=\"s2\">”Autodesk CEO Carl Bass </span>在<a href=\"http://inthefold.autodesk.com/in_the_fold/2014/05/accelerating-the-future-of-3d-printing.html\">发布<span class=\"s2\"> Spark </span>的官方博客里</a>写道。这款尚未命名的<span class=\"s2\"> 3D </span>打印机将完全开源，其它厂商也可以使用它的设计。\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">\r\n\t<img src=\"img/uploads/20160605203719iqA4vLzpkN6fRDxT.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.6984375\" data-format=\"jpeg\"> \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\" style=\"text-align:center;\">\r\n\tSLA 打印出的作品，来自 <a href=\"http://www.artcorp.com/resins.html\" target=\"_blank\">ArtCorp</a> \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">\r\n\t大约<a href=\"http://www.yicai.com/news/2014/02/3521157.html\">从<span class=\"s3\"> 2010 </span>年起</a>，<span class=\"s3\">Autodesk </span>开始加大传统桌面设计软件之外的投入，寻求新的机遇。Autodesk 在那年成立消费产品事业部，通过自行研发或收购建立起一系列针对消费者的软件和在线应用，比如<span class=\"s3\"> Sketchbook</span>、<span class=\"s3\">Homestyler </span>和<span class=\"s3\"> Pixlr</span>。最近的一次相关收购在今年<span class=\"s3\"> 3 </span>月，<span class=\"s3\">Autodesk </span>买下了数字创意产品集市<span class=\"s3\"> <a href=\"https://creativemarket.com/\">Creative Market</a></span>。\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\">\r\n\t<span class=\"s1\">创客运动升温后，</span>Autodesk <span class=\"s1\">也积极投入其中，收购了汇集大量</span> DIY <span class=\"s1\">教程的社区</span> <a href=\"http://www.instructables.com/\">Instructables</a><span class=\"s1\">、赞助了<a href=\"http://www.techdrafts.com/post/44276388917/techshop-sf\">旧金山<span class=\"s3\"> TechShop</span></a></span> <span class=\"s1\">和各地</span> Maker Faire<span class=\"s1\">。</span>Autodesk <span class=\"s1\">的轻量级设计软件</span> 123D <span class=\"s1\">也被包括</span> MakerBot <span class=\"s1\">在内的多家</span> 3D <span class=\"s1\">打印机制造商推荐给用户。</span> \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">\r\n\t按照<span class=\"s3\"> Autodesk </span>的设想，<span class=\"s3\">Spark </span>将成为<span class=\"s3\"> 3D </span>打印机的操作系统和软件，类似<span class=\"s3\"> Android </span>之于智能手机的角色。\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">\r\n\t<span class=\"s3\">“</span>设计一样东西和将它打印出来这两部之间并不连贯。我看到现在有<span class=\"s3\"> 40 </span>种不同的<span class=\"s3\"> 3D </span>打印机软件，制约了<span class=\"s3\"> 3D </span>打印的发展。<span class=\"s3\">”</span>产品发布后，<span class=\"s3\">Carl Bass </span>在<a href=\"http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2014/05/14/autodesk-unveils-open-source-3-d-printing-system/\">接受《纽约时报》采访时</a>说道。\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">\r\n\t桌面<span class=\"s3\"> 3D </span>打印市场原本有开源的商业产品<span class=\"s3\"> MakerBot </span>可以参考。但当<span class=\"s3\"> 1:1 </span>山寨产品在中国出现后，<span class=\"s3\">MakerBot </span>联合创始人<span class=\"s3\"> Bre Pettis </span>在<span class=\"s3\"> 2012 </span>年<a href=\"http://www.makerbot.com/blog/2012/09/24/lets-try-that-again/\">宣布不再开源</a>，并将另一位联合创始人<span class=\"s3\"> <a href=\"http://www.techdrafts.com/post/43555376522/shenzhen-makers\">Zach Smith</a> </span>赶出公司。\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">\r\n\t<span class=\"s2\">Autodesk </span>的产品有望填补这个空白，让其它<span class=\"s3\"> 3D </span>打印机制造商在它的基础上开发更好的软件和硬件。\r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p4\">\r\n\tSpark <span class=\"s1\">将与</span> <a href=\"http://reprap.org/wiki/RepRap\">RepRap</a><span class=\"s1\">、<a href=\"http://www.eventorbot.com/\"><span class=\"s3\">Eventorbot</span></a></span> <span class=\"s1\">和</span> <a href=\"http://www.tantillus.org/Home.html\">Tantillus</a> <span class=\"s1\">等现有的开源倡议结合起来。凭借</span> Autodesk <span class=\"s1\">的营销力量和它在工业领域的影响力，</span>Spark <span class=\"s1\">应该会很顺利。</span> \r\n</p>\r\n<p class=\"p3\">\r\n\t按计划，<span class=\"s2\">Spark </span>和<span class=\"s2\"> Autodesk </span>自己的<span class=\"s3\"> 3D </span>打印机将在今年晚些时候面市。不过根据发布的时间点，本周末在旧金山湾区的<span class=\"s3\"> Maker Faire </span>上我们或许就会看到<span class=\"s3\"> Spark </span>甚至打印机的雏形。\r\n</p>\n\n\n"}